modules.description: Encodes and decodes values between a custom type and strings, with support for partial decoding that returns remaining input. Handles structured data represented as a variant type with specific constructors. Used to serialize and deserialize configuration settings during runtime parsing.

Provides decoding and encoding functions for CBOR data format, supporting integers, floats, strings, lists, and maps. Processes binary input and generates corresponding OCaml values, and vice versa. Enables efficient serialization of structured data for network communication or file storage.

Encodes and decodes custom data types to and from CBOR-encoded strings, supporting partial parsing and structured variants. Key operations include serialization of configuration-like data and deserialization with input tracking. It enables efficient data exchange by converting between in-memory variants and compact binary representations. Examples include parsing incomplete network packets and storing structured settings in a binary format.
